## 5. MANIFEST FORMAT (inception.json)

**Schema File:** `/Users/damianpiatkowski/Code/inception-engine/src/schemas/manifest.ts`

### Top-Level Structure
```typescript
interface Manifest {
  skills: SkillEntry[];
  files?: FileEntry[];
  configs?: ConfigEntry[];
  mcpServers?: McpServerEntry[];
  agentRules?: AgentRuleEntry[];
}
```

### Entry Types

#### SkillEntry
```typescript
{
  name: string;              // Alphanumeric + [._-], must not start with dot
  path: string;              // Relative path to skill source directory
  agents: AgentId[];         // Which agents this skill targets
}
```
- Source must be a directory
- Must contain `SKILL.md` file
- Only symlink/copy (no modification)

#### FileEntry
```typescript
{
  name: string;
  path: string;              // Relative path to source file
  target: string;            // Target template: {home}/{appdata}/{xdg_config} + path
  agents: AgentId[];
}
```
- Single file deployment
- Target must stay within placeholder root

#### ConfigEntry
```typescript
{
  name: string;
  target: string;            // Target JSON config file
  patch: Record<string, unknown>;  // JSON merge-patch to apply
  agents: AgentId[];
}
```
- Applies RFC 7386 merge-patch semantics
- Stores undo-patch for reversible changes
- Prevents double-patching same config by different skills

#### McpServerEntry
```typescript
{
  name: string;
  agents: AgentId[];
  config: Record<string, unknown>;  // Raw server descriptor
}
```
- Compiled to config-patch for agent-specific MCP config files
- Agent adapters validate config shape

#### AgentRuleEntry
```typescript
{
  name: string;
  agents: AgentId[];
  path: string;              // Relative path to rules/instruction file
}
```
- Single instruction/rules file
- Compiled to file-write deployment

### Target Template Format
```
{home}/.claude/settings.json
{appdata}/MyApp/config.json
{xdg_config}/opencode/settings.json
```
- Placeholders: `{home}`, `{appdata}`, `{xdg_config}`
- Cannot escape placeholder root with `..`

